    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/built-in-plugins/processes/autoruns/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/built-in-plugins/processes/autoruns/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;h3&gt;High‑level description&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;highlevel-description&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#highlevel-description&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Autoruns&lt;/strong&gt; plug‑in parses CSV files produced by the Windows Autoruns utility, extracting entries that define programs or scripts that start automatically. It reads registry locations, file paths and related metadata to enumerate persistence mechanisms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Reveals what programs are set to execute on boot or login.&lt;br&gt;
- Shows whether each autorun entry is active or disabled.&lt;br&gt;
- Identifies the exact file or command that will be launched.&lt;br&gt;
- Links each entry to its user profile, aiding attribution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;File:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;configuration/autoruns.xml&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Plugin parser:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;Csv&lt;/code&gt; parser (built‑in CSV parser)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Timeline data&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;timeline-data&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#timeline-data&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;The timeline displays the following elements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
  &lt;thead&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;th&gt;Timeline field&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th&gt;Value&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/thead&gt;
  &lt;tbody&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Description&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;entry&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Full registry key of the autorun entry (combined &lt;em&gt;Entry Location&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Entry&lt;/em&gt;).&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Additional Description&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;image_path&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Path to the executable or file that will be run automatically.&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;enabled&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Boolean indicating if the autorun entry is enabled.&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;category&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Classification of the autorun (e.g., Startup, Run, Service).&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;profile&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;User profile context associated with the autorun entry.&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Fields&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;fields&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#fields&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;table&gt;
